Pre-Game Insights: The Proteas are scheduled to play England and Bangladesh at the Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai on the 21st and 24th of October.
While the match between South Africa and England is expected to be clear, the match against Bangladesh might just fall in the eye of the storm.

The India Meteorological Department (IMD) has predicted a potential cyclonic storm emerging in the southeastern Arabian Sea and the nearby Lakshadweep region within the next 48 hours due to a low-pressure area expected to develop in the Arabian Sea.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The ongoing match between South Africa and the Netherlands in Dharamsala was also delayed due to rain and was reduced to 43-overs per side.
The weather is expected to be clear for the rest of the match.
South Africa's past World Cup exits due to rain-affected matches in 1992 and 2003 were highlighted as historical comparisons.
